"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1927874-Paris-Olympics-athlete-pay-2024-money\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Athletes competing in the2024 Olympic Games in Pariscould be set for a hefty payday if they secure gold.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}, {\"ngram\": \"the2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 43}, {\"ngram\": \"Pariscould\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 57}, {\"ngram\": \"a hefty payday\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 83}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 103}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The summer sporting spectacle commences on Friday, July 26, with a plethora of competitors vying to etch their names into history as the best in their respective disciplines.\", \"from\": 107, \"to\": 281, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The summer\", \"from\": 107, \"to\": 117}, {\"ngram\": \"spectacle commences\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 146}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 156}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 162}, {\"ngram\": \"a plethora\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 182}, {\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 186, \"to\": 197}, {\"ngram\": \"their names\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 223}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 236}, {\"ngram\": \"their respective disciplines\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's not just glory on the line over the coming weeks, there is also a substantial prize pot available for the top performers.\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 413, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"glory\", \"from\": 301, \"to\": 306}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 318}, {\"ngram\": \"the coming weeks\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 340}, {\"ngram\": \"a substantial prize pot\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 379}, {\"ngram\": \"the top performers\", \"from\": 394, \"to\": 412}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although theInternational Olympic Committeedoesn't provide prize money to participants or medal winners,National Olympic Committeesoften reward their triumphant athletes.\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 584, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theInternational Olympic Committeedoesn't\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 464}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 484}, {\"ngram\": \"participants\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"medal winners\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 517}, {\"ngram\": \"National Olympic Committeesoften\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"their triumphant athletes\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 583}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athleticshas revealed that they will be awarding \\u00a338,700 in prize money to gold medallists in track and field events for the first time ever, while theInternational Boxing Association (IBA)has declared a whopping \\u00a32.4million payout to this summer's medallists.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.9999999741603464, \"rank\": 2.582861787435163e-08, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Athleticshas\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 604}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 663}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medallists\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"track and field events\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"IBA)has\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 784}, {\"ngram\": \"a whopping \\u00a32.4million payout\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 823}, {\"ngram\": \"this summer's medallists\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 851}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medal-winning boxers are set to receive \\u00a338,700, according to reports, while those securing silver will receive \\u00a319,300 and bronze medallists will pocket \\u00a39,600.\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 1019, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gold medal-winning boxers\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"reports\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 927}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze medallists\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 999}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The payouts from National Committees vary based on location.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The payouts\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1032}, {\"ngram\": \"National Committees\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1057}, {\"ngram\": \"location\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1080}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, Australia's Medal Incentive Funding Programme typically awards athletes \\u00a310,137 ($20,000) for gold, \\u00a37,603 ($15,000) for silver, and \\u00a35,067 ($10,000) for bronze, whereas the USA reportedly pays out respective amounts of \\u00a329,103 ($37,500), \\u00a317,462 ($22,500) and \\u00a311,644 ($15,000), reportsthe Mirror.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1096, \"end\": 1105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9095922179530044, \"rank\": 0.0955957353510825, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1270, \"end\": 1273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9979915382633029, \"rank\": 0.002011814639314943, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1094}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1217, \"to\": 1223}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1256}, {\"ngram\": \"respective amounts\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1312}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a stark contrast to Team GB athletes, who reportedly receive no financial reward for securing a podium finish at the Olympic Games, Singapore has announced it would award its athletes up to \\u00a3776,000 ($1million) for winning gold at the Tokyo Olympics 2021.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1419, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999976954558585, \"rank\": 2.3045457655916885e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1531, \"end\": 1540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9996716760077163, \"rank\": 0.0003284299286899093, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a stark contrast\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"no financial reward\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1479}, {\"ngram\": \"a podium finish\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1529}, {\"ngram\": \"its athletes\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1582}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1648}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes from New Zealand, Norway and Sweden will also receive nothing for a podium placement.\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1682, \"end\": 1688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8431966885930048, \"rank\": 0.17091745885771922, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1693, \"end\": 1699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"score\": 0.9667315144880156, \"rank\": 0.028294362640583368, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"New Zealand\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1680}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1725}, {\"ngram\": \"a podium placement\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, National Olympic Committees' prize pots are not the only source of income for Olympians.\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1760, \"end\": 1787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9017101490394911, \"rank\": 0.10900382020224893, \"text\": \"National Olympic Committees\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only source\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"income\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 1847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lucrative sponsorship and endorsement deals can also provide substantial earnings.\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1931, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Lucrative sponsorship and endorsement deals\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1892}, {\"ngram\": \"substantial earnings\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, some athletes maintain full-time jobs while pursuing their Olympic dreams ahead of the Paris 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some athletes\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"full-time jobs